summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed, executed on the 27th day of October, A. D., 1890, by the Spring Hill Water Company, by Jacob Furth, its vice president and John Leary, its secretary, to the City of Seattle, for Lots 1 to 6 inc., Block 3, J. C. Kinnears Addition; Lots 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 9, & 10, Block 6; Lots 3, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, & 10, Block 7; Lots 8, 9 & 10, Block 8; Lots 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 9 &10, Block 9; Lot 11, Block 5, and all of Block 15, Central Addition; Lot 7, Block 1; Lots 1, 2, 7 & 8, Block 3; and Lots 1 & 2, Block 4, McNaught's 3rd Addition; Lots 1, 2, 3 & 4, Block 37, Blocks 38, 63, 64 except Lot 1, and Block 84, Burke's 2nd Addition; part of Block 85, C. C. Terry's 2nd Addition; a certain tract in Section 32, Township 25 North, Range 4 East, and a certain tract in Section 10, Township 24 North, Range 4 East.
